      <story-so-far>
        <reasoning>This passage documents the completion of Kira's dietary assessment and the plant collective's ability to synthesize and safely test food from fungal/mushroom chemistry. I replaced the previous note that a dietary assessment was only scheduled with concrete outcomes (assessment completed, tests run, meal synthesized and eaten). I consolidated medical treatment and daily-wellness items into fewer bullets to keep the summary compact while preserving ongoing care and recovery status. I retained key unresolved items (Biological Samples container, offline ship AI, limited ship supplies, life-support time estimate) because they remain plot-relevant.</reasoning>
        <summary>
          - Shuttle carrying mining/terraforming supplies and a container labeled “Biological Samples” failed during approach; cargo struck the hull and the shuttle crashed; Kira Voss survived while several crew members, including the pilots, were killed.
          - Shipboard AI SAM is offline; emergency protocols brought Kira’s neural link online and instantiated a childlike assistant AI called Buddy; external communications and the ship’s distress beacon are broken.
          - Hull breach exposed breathable atmosphere and alien vegetation; the shuttle served as temporary shelter and rescue is uncertain (weeks to months).
          - Salvageable ship supplies are limited (small quantities of sealed water, several days of rations and medical supplies); ship life support is on emergency power with roughly 48 hours remaining.
          - The Biological Samples container remains active, glowing, drawing power, and cannot be shut down.
          - Buddy located a freshwater source; Kira left the shuttle with a bleeding leg, encountered sentient plant entities (Scout and larger cooperative spheres), and was offered care and transport by the plant collective (including an entity named Holloway).
          - Kira was brought to Central Coordination (a living vine structure); intake recorded her identity, injuries and lack of communicator, and scheduled orientation and medical evaluation.
          - Kira passed orientation and met Remedy, a salvage-built humanoid robot doctor that uses cultivated mushrooms to synthesize medicines; Remedy halted infection in Kira’s leg with a fungal treatment and plant-fiber bandages, prescribed ongoing daily wound care with full healing estimated in ~two weeks.
          - Kira slept ~9 hours, woke with stable vitals, and remains in temporary quarters under continuous care and companionship from Scout, Buddy, Holloway and Remedy.
          - Dietary assessment completed: Holloway administered detailed nutrition forms; Kira reports no religious/cultural restrictions, mild lactose intolerance, and a preference for protein-rich foods with moderate spice tolerance.
          - Remedy can synthesize complete proteins, carbohydrates and some fats from cultivated mushrooms, but vitamins are more difficult; novel fungal proteins require staged allergy testing.
          - Remedy and Buddy ran stepwise allergy/tolerance tests (small doses with observation windows) across ~8–10 fungal-derived compounds; most compounds were approved after testing.
          - Remedy synthesized a nutritionally complete ~800-calorie meal from mushroom-derived compounds; Kira ate it (found it unpalatable but nutritious), digestive tolerance check scheduled in 30 minutes, and a three-times-daily meal schedule was set.
          - Kira’s nutrition stabilized and her adaptation to life in the plant collective progressed; Remedy, Holloway, Scout and Buddy continue to coordinate her care.
        </summary>
      </story-so-far>
      <emotional-journey>
        <reasoning>POV feelings — Kira moves here between amused delight, curious fascination, and cautious relief. The intake questionnaire and the absurdity of "culture" questions make her laugh and lighten her mood; the technical testing of novel fungal proteins introduces a low-level clinical unease (unknown reactions) that she manages pragmatically; finally, actually eating and metabolically responding produces a strong, physical relief and emotional acceptance. Reader experience — mostly warmth, amused incredulity, and reassurance. The scene is low-threat domestic comedy: the reader is invited to chuckle at the plants' bureaucracy, enjoy Remedy's practical competence, and relax as a concrete survival need (food) is met. Multiple beats — yes: playful/curious humor, a brief procedural anxiety, then comforting relief — rather than one single dominant tone, though the overall tone is upbeat and gently whimsical. Comparison to prior pattern — this continues the ongoing arc from trauma/isolation toward trust and integration. Earlier beats rose from dread to wonder and cautious trust; this scene consolidates that shift by converting an existential need (nutrition) into a routine that is odd but dependable. Surprises — none significant here: the plants' paperwork, Buddy's helpfulness, and Remedy's synthesis are all developments already established; the passage deepens them but does not contradict expectations. Character change — Kira further cements her willingness to participate and take agency: she suggests process improvement (start tests while finishing forms), accepts the alien testing protocol, endures and reframes an awful-tasting but life-restoring meal, and mentally accepts this as “my life now.” This is a continued trust-building and acceptance beat rather than a sudden transformation.</reasoning>
        <beats>
          <beat tags="humor, joy">Playful amusement and curiosity as Kira fills out the extensive dietary forms and delights at the absurdity of alien HR-style questions. She laughs at the idea of being asked about religious dietary rules after a crash and genuinely enjoys watching Remedy and the fungi work. The reader shares light amusement and warmth — a comic, humanizing moment that reduces tension.</beat>
          <beat tags="unease, suspense">Low-level clinical anxiety during the allergy/novel-protein testing. Kira feels pragmatic concern about reacting to unfamiliar fungal proteins and waits through timed tests. The reader experiences mild suspense and empathic nervousness — this is procedural danger (possible allergic reaction) rather than existential threat.</beat>
          <beat tags="relief, acceptance">Physical and emotional relief when the compounds pass tests and Kira eats a nutritionally complete but unpalatable meal. The act of eating fills the bodily hollowness, calms shaking, and produces affectionate amusement at the meal’s awful taste. The reader feels reassured — a concrete survival problem is solved — and witnesses Kira accept her new quotidian reality with gratitude and humor.</beat>
        </beats>
